doc_summary_long: A British man has been found dead near an airport in Málaga, southern Spain. His hands and feet had been bound to a bench and his trousers were around his ankles, according to reports. Spanish detectives are investigating after the man, named in reports as Steven Allford, 51, was discovered by a security guard on Friday morning between the airport's train station and the terminal building. Spanish media reported that the body showed no visible signs of violence, although there were signs he had been drinking. A postmortem examination is due to be carried out at Málaga's Institute of Medicine.
doc_summary_short: A British man has been found dead near an airport in Málaga, southern Spain. His hands and feet had been bound to a bench and his trousers were around his ankles, according to reports.
doc_title: British man found dead and bound to bench at Málaga airport
